Muhammad Bashir, Lokoja Hajia Rabiat Bello, an elder sister to Kogi State Governor, Yahaya Bello is dead. Hajia Rabiat, 57, passed away, after a protracted illness at her Okene residence. In the announcement personally signed by the governor, on behalf of the family, the the late Hajia Rabiat died late on Monday. “With total submission to the Will of Almighty Allah, the family of Alhaji Bello Ipemida Ochi regret to announce the death of their beloved daughter Hajia Rabiat Bello following a protracted illness at the age of 59. “The sad event took place in the late hours of Monday  23rd of December, 2019,” Governor Bello said in announcement he personally signed on Tuesday the family. It was learnt that the deceased would be buried today in Okene according to Islamic rites. 